completion: Our first room the carpet was wet. Changed to another room. The beds were so worn couldn’t hardly stay in bed they were broken down at the edges. Sink didn’t drain, drawers were broken, shower handle wouldn’t stay in place for the temperature control. Changed to another room.  The toilet tank has a large crack. Air conditioner leaked so bad we laid towels down to soak up the water and it was so bad the towels could be wrung out.  Very moldy.  Found a dead cockroach the 3 night.  The morning we checked out a 4 inch cockroach came out from under the sofa. The floor was saturated for about 8 feet.  3 of us have acute sinus infections and sore throats from living in this roach and mold infested room.  The problem is they don’t have other rooms to move you to because of being fully booked. They say they will send maintenance to check the problem but they don’t show up. The place needs a major remodel. The breakfast was meh. They had a hard time keeping up with filling the empty items and rarely wiped off the tables.  I have been a Hilton Honors member for many years and have stayed many times in the Hilton family hotels. This was the worse hotel I have ever stayed in.  I would never recommend this hotel to anyone.     I also don’t understand why when I checked my review I attached photos of the wet towels and the large cockroach  they are not showing the photos on my post.  This hotel needs to be completely transparent in letting customers show the conditions of your hotel.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: pros, beach, oceanfront.
completion:
The pros were the location, the view and the walk to the beach. We paid for an oceanfront view, and the view was gorgeous. Breakfast was also great. Most of the staff we interacted with were lovely.

I don’t usually nitpick, but I was paying $400 a night and find some things just not excusable at that price.
They don’t have daily maid service, and you have to go down to get towels/toilet paper and take out your own trash. Again, for the price I was paying, I think daily service would be expected. You can only get a full service every 5 days.
They are dog friendly, which is amazing…but there was no place to take them to the bathroom. The abandoned lot next door was what we opted for, but it was filled with thorny and burred plants. They are not allowed on the beach (city law) so there are really no options. At one point we tried to use a tiny patch of grass outside the fence, but the bartender from the pool told us it was gross to have them within eyesight and we needed to take our dogs off property to use the bathroom.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: beach, place, room.
completion: The place is perfect for us. Walking distance going to the beach. The room is clean when we coming in but after few days they never clean even we request in the front desk. That's the bad part. The breakfast is great.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, beach, budget.
completion: Nice budget friendly hotel on the beach. Nothing special, but no complaints!

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: rooms, beach, tub.
completion: Rooms were mediocre but the view of the beach is amazing. They didn't have a restaurant but the people are friendly. Loved the pool area and hot tub. Never even saw the Tiki bar.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hampton, guests, coffee.
completion: Can’t go wrong with Hampton! One star off because they would not make coffee at 6pm. I know that’s late for coffee but my fiancé drinks coffee all day every day, also when your spending 250.00 a night. Make your guests coffee.

prompt: Write a 2.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, lounge, room.
completion:
For nearly $500/night, I was expecting more than the standard hotel however, it was nothing more than average.  The front desk was nice but I had to walk by an overly full garbage can when walking in, so that set the tone. I wouldn’t mind really, but it was that way every day that I was there. The can in the pool area was also overflowing by lunch and never changed until the end of the day.
This place has a smaller than average pool with very little seating. Approx 20 lounge chairs and there was room for many more. There were no umbrellas or tables In the pool area and very little shade.  There is a small bar outside that had some shaded seating. Prices for cocktails was $12+ .  Bring your ant spray, as there was an abundance of ants around the pool.  The breakfast seating area is a decent size but it doesn’t accommodate the amount of people that can stay at that hotel. I know it’s not reasonable to plan for every patron to eat breakfast at the same time however, when it’s 15-20 min wait to make a waffle or wait on some other item to come out so you can have something before they close the doors on you, then it’s a problem.
Our room had a rusted, I mean RUSTED, like throw it away it’s so rusty, lamp.

Room was very clean, gulf view, great AC, and it was quiet. Across the street are a few restaurants, walking distance to Starbucks. Publix and Walmart very close by.

Construction is starting next door on new giant condos so the peace and quiet May be gone soon…. That’s also the same side as the bar.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: beach, breakfast, costumer.
completion: Great breakfast. Close to beach beautiful ocean view. Wonderful costumer service. Very nice employees.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hampton, inns.
completion:
First of all, the few employees they had working were friendly and helpful but there were not many.   I had to go down to the desk to pick up fresh towels daily and I emptied our trash myself.   It was entirely self catering with no maid service at all.  We were there four days and nobody swept our room or even the hallway.

The room seemed clean but there were small things like the old coffee pods were left in the pots from the former visitors and one bedspread had a nasty looking stain. I took the spread down and asked for a replacement but they did not have any.

On the positive side, the breakfasts were very plentiful and tasty.  We would have liked it if the hotel had kept the coffee available all day like other Hampton Inns do but they did give us coffee packets so we could make it in our room.

We stayed in one of the suites and it was a nice room.  It's getting a little dated but not too bad.   The view from the 9th floor was wonderful.  We enjoyed sitting on the balcony, though one of the chairs was missing a leg.  Requests for an additional chair were ignored.  Luckily we had brought some beach chairs.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, beach, visit.
completion: Best hotel for a weekend stay! Always worth the money, good location and right on the beach. Good breakfast and staff is always so nice. Amazing tiki bar and beautiful view. This is my 3rd or 4th time staying and I will continue to come back to this hotel anytime I visit orange beach! This photo is only yards away from the hotel after walking out over the short bridge!

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: beach, rooms, balcony.
completion: This is the PERFECT place for families with kids who want to getaway to the beach! In the morning breakfast is made for you (eggs/omelettes, fruit, cereal, waffles, yogurt) then just head out to the beach. It's literally just a few steps out there, then spend the day between there and the pool and hot tub. They have a bar open just a few days a week, the gym is huge and BEAUTIFUL ocean view while you work out! The gym has quite a few treadmills, ellipticals, weights and thoughtful extras like a private bathroom and cold filtered water dispenser. We get a balcony room with a studio (basically a divided room with a couch and chair on one side, beds on the other) and they do have adjoining rooms for larger families. The gulf view is amazing. The whole place is just so relaxed and chill! Our rooms have included mini fridge and microwave which comes in handy. The rooms are very clean and seem well-maintained. All front desk and breakfast staff have been so nice and helpful. They do have laundry, 2nd floor (across from the gym) and it's $1.50 in quarters per wash or dry cycle. Definitely recommend, we will be back!

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: jett, bryan, bar.
completion: One word..... Awesome...hada wait a coupla hours for a room so we hung out at the bar with Bryan Jett. He was amazing...

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hampton, beach.
completion:
💙💜⛱️What a wonderful stay here! Employees are firendly at the front desk and the cleaning team.

Rooms are pretty plain and simple, but that doesnt matter. I cant imagine many people will spend much time in their room, except to sleep.🛌 The hotel🏢 is directly on the beach! 🏖👐🙌👏

A lounge chair rental service w is available for rent at $35 a day. You can walk directly from the hotel to the beach via a wooden  boardwalk w a few stairs. The white sand is so soft and the sound of the waves just took our stress away. ⛱️

Outside pool and hottub also face the beach.

Parking permit for the garage at check in. Easily elevator access frlm the garage too.

Most rooms with balconies facing the ocean are double beds🛌 instead of kings, which could be good for families.

🧽Very clean, did I mention clean!!!🧼 Absolutely will return to this Hampton when we are in town again. Very satisfied multi year diamond member here.

There is an outside tiki bar for drinks and the full beach affect too! 🍸🍷🍹

During the stay a 🌀storm blew in and it was very cold, so we hit the hot tub. I saw alot of kiddos playing in the pool and a few adults. It is a heated pool, but not as warm as the hot tub🏟, so the hot tub it was for me.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: ocean, location, experience.
completion: Great location and prices. Helped shape my first ocean experience splendidly.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: room, furniture, ocean.
completion: Excellent views of the ocean.  Free breakfast and free parking.  The lobby is updated and the staff maintains a daily activity board each morning.  The furniture in our room had some staining and the ceiling had remnants of water damage.  Those things didn't hamper our fun though.  Overall, it was a great stay especially when you can use points to cover the price of the room.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, inn, guests.
completion:
We stayed here for several nights. It was our first visit to the Gulf Shores/Orange Beach area. This inn was a nice little place to stay.
The hotel itself is in decent condition with updated modern designs and comfort. The doors going into the room and balcony could have used a little maintenence. The room had a spectacular view of the Gulf and we enjoy the balcony alot. The pool/hottub was clean enough and a had great temps every time. Their beach area was always kept nice and we spent alot of time just enjoying the waves.
The breakfast was always served hot and there was always plenty even though we often ate towards the end of the meal time. They serve you instead of you picking what you want - Covid19 restrictions.
The only reason they are losing a star - we had to ask for everything. Since they are not cleaning the rooms and restocking supplies and clean towels each day, we were left to ask for toilet paper, new paper cups, coffee, etc. Several times it seemed as though they didn't want to get anything for us and that we were imposing on them to ask for a trash bags or whatever. I would suggest having a time frame each morning that the guests could get what they need without "disturbing" the front desk staff. Other than that the staff was pleasant.
One of the elevators was out of service the entire time we were there. Apparently it has been out for several weeks.. while most of time it wasn't too long of a wait, during the weekends it got a little crazy.
The Tiki bartender (Oscar) is funny! Enjoy as few beers with him.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: beach, balcony, clean.
completion: Very clean and keep well. There is a parking deck which makes parking somewhat difficult when u have a larger vehicle. We had pizza delivered and the staff offered us plates & napkins. The beach is clean. No building on one side so plenty of room to spread out. Heated pool and hot tub. Nice balcony to enjoy the view. Bad side: the walls are PAPER THIN! We heard every conversation in the hallways and could hear when the room next door flushed the toilet.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: beach, hotel, guests.
completion: A section of the beach is dedicated to hotel guests, and there are large beach umbrellas and sturdy beach chairs with wooden frames available for rental. Though nothing else compares to the emerald green waters and the sugar sand, there is also an indoor and an outdoor swimming pool. Our stay was short, just a couple of nights and one full day, but we enjoyed it very much. We particularly enjoyed our meal at the open-air restaurant by the outdoor pool. We also enjoyed our first floor room with quick access to the beach, and the room was very clean and well-maintained. The gift shop was open until ten and had candy and soft drinks to satisfy my late night craving for chocolate. The staff was great. October was a great time for a visit to The Emerald Coast.

prompt: Write a 2.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: stay, room, beach.
completion: We decided to stay there because for the  beach location which is so awesome.  Our room was fine until we found out that the roof in the bathroom was with mold we called the reception and the answered was the could chance to another room but it will complete different which mean that we paid for beach view and we will get something not good for us.  The room service that we supposedly  get daily it wasn't true. We stay for 5 days and we only got 2 days. We have to request for it. And the shower wasn't eaither clean Not everything was bad, the pool, the restaurants services and the valet parking did an amazing job.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: gulf, pools, pool.
completion: Had a good experience here in February.  Gulf water was only about 63 degrees but you can go in for some quick dips.  Huge pool deck with multiple food shops and pools.  One of the outdoor pools was heated.  Would stay here again!

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: beach, pools, tub.
completion: Stayed here athe end of October and beginning of November.  It was their off season and the place was quite.  Perfect for those who want to feel the place is theirs alone with several outdoor pools and a hot tub, along with an indoor pool and hot tub if it gets too cold.  The staff are very accommodating and friendly.  One of the best things is to have both the sunrise and sunset visable right on the beach.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: beach, rooms, vacation.
completion: Very nice view and lovely beach. Rooms were a little outdated and could use some love. The staff was kind of iffy... One of my servers was really rude for no reason. Overall a nice place to vacation.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: hilton, staff, resort.
completion: All the staff we interacted with were wonderful! Rooms were clean and very nice, if you stay definitely take advantage of the shuttle service it saves a ton on parking!! This is a wonderful resort for families to relax and spend time together! Hilton, GREAT JOB!!!

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: resort, hilton, beachview.
completion: I loved this resort up until today. I have visited several times since last year, and have never had 1 problem. My previous visits, the rooms were dated, with a musty, moldy odor. We were on the 7th floor where the toilets were way too small.  They were very low to the floor. But, Crystal Haire, the AWESOME Front Office Supervisor, was very nice and professional. She upgraded both my rooms to the newly renovated rooms, with a perfect beachview! Both my rooms are junior deluxe suits, with two queen beds with pull out lamps on both sides of the bed, one sofa bed, and two junior beds. Each junior bed has their very own tv. The bathroom has the barnyard sliding door, and the rooms are cooling much better than before, as the vent was in the corner, blocked by the curtain, and in an area where is was impossible to cool the room properly. Now there are 2 vents located in a proper area to cool the room properly. Estelle is also very nice, friendly, and personable. She works the food and beverage area. She has a great personality. It goes a long way with me. This is a great resort, in a very nice location. I have 6 of my family members here for the very 1st time. They wanted to the beautiful water. The tides were up, so We couldn't get into the water. The water was barely touching our feet, as so many others. Hilton's beach police/security drove up to us us specifically, and told us that we couldn't allow the water to touch our feet. We were all stunned, because there were so many others doing the exact same thing. Even further into the water. He drove off, and some non-blacks asked what did he say to us, and we told her. This one in particular was saddened! She said look at all these other doing the same, and some are practically swimming, and nothing has been said to them. I actually wanted to leave, and go home. We hadn't been there for 5 minutes when he came up to us. This occurred around 10 a.m., so you'll know who was on duty.  But, I'm yet here with my family. Please see pictures of others walking through the water. Prejudice is very much alive. Other than this, you all would get 5 plus stars. Hayden Edelman and Kimberly Arnold at PICNIX, the ice cream parlour were very nice, friendly, and professional.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: balcony, rooms, ocean.
completion: The rooms are warmly decorated, comfortable and a delight for our stay of four days for a conference.  The balcony is a great place to soak in the ocean air, delight in the surf sounds and beautiful view.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: beach, hotel, sandestin.
completion: Beautiful hotel with all the possible amenities.   If you want a big hotel with nice rooms, friendly staff, many restaurant choices at the hotel and near by this hotel is a great choice.   The pools were very nice and the location is perfect on the beach.   The Gulf coast is gorgeous.   Sandestin is a very congested area with so many people on the beach and at all the restaurants but they do a wonderful job at managing it all.   If you are looking for a hotel that goes all out for the 4th of July this is your place.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: spa, cabanas, beach.
completion: From the awesome spa to the food everything was super exoens7ve but well worth every penny!   Also I cannot say enough about the view from my room the pictures say it all.  3 pools a great, steakhouse, cabanas, jet ski rental right on beach, golf, a gym, a staff that in my opinion very likely to be unmatched on their professionalism amd friendliness, and I could go on.   I went for the weekend but stays 5 days instead.  To be noted I went alone on this trip.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: destin, resort, beach.
completion: The Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort and Spa has my vote. I booked this place because I wanted to be on the beach surrounded by gorgeous views. This is my 4th trip to Destin, and I wanted a no worries vacation. I was able to walk right on the beach from the hotel. One can rent chairs and umbrellas from 9-5 or bring their own. The beach is super clean with powdery sand perfect for strolling, building sand castles, playing volleyball, etc. Additionally, jet ski and banana boats are available within a short few paces. I’ve been satisfied with the hotel/room amenities, restaurants, indoor/outdoor pools and hot tubs. I’m ready to rebook this hotel for another vacation in the near future. The property is enjoyable for families, couples, and solo travelers!

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: rooms, beach, hilton.
completion: The beach was lovely, they have an indoor pool and outdoor pool and spa.  The people who work here pleasant. The downside for the Hilton name these rooms did not live up. One air conditioning vent for the whole room, in Florida, in the middle of the night my husband and I had to kick off the covers we were sweating and we had the room set to 60. Couldn’t find the TV remote control anywhere in the room but we didn’t come to watch TV that’s just a point. When it comes to our view everyone else has an open balcony view of the ocean we have wood and the roof of the building behind us.   The dj and pool patrons where right under our room and exquisitely loud.   This is where the tv remote would have come in handy.   If we stay here again it will not be in room 228

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: resort, beach, visit.

The restaurants and gift shop on the resort were so good. The beach was perfect. I had a wonderful time and can't wait to plan my next visit here.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, beaches, recommend.

First vacation in two years and soooooo worth the wait! Hotel property is well kept and clean. Staff are friendly and eager to help when needed.

How about the beaches…absolutely incredible with the best sand ever! Water is clean and not freezing cold.

Highly recommend!!

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, beach, rooms.
completion:

The bad: housekeeping shows up occasionally, rooms are showing signs of wear. We had a collapsing ceiling in the shower and a musty smelling room.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: destin, resort, hotel.
completion: Had never been to Destin before, but this was a lovely surprise.  The hotel is gorgeous, the staff were nice and my very favorites were the folks who brought drinks out to those of us occupying the beach chairs.  It's an enormous resort with golfing etc, but my friend and I are all about beach sitting.

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, beach, spacious.
completion: Beautiful, modern hotel with friendly staff, spacious rooms, and amazing beach access!

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, recommend, highly.
completion:
My husband and I just came back from our small vacation, it was a really nice and beautiful experience with this hotel!!
Nice atmosphere, clean and great service!!  Even the food was so good and delicious.. we enjoyed our trip a lot and we will come back soon.. really highly recommend it

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Resort hotel, with the following keywords: beach, came, tub.
completion: Absolutely LOVED my stay and can't wait to come back again! Great service and even though we came at a spring chilly season the pools and hot tub were AMAZING! Breakfast was definitely a highlight for the mornings before walking on the beach!

prompt: Write a 5.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, rooms, room.
completion: Nice, clean and expansive hotel. We booked a basic room with 2 queen beds. The room was extremely spacious and could have fit 2 king beds with room to spare in the sleeping area. Rooms are not super-up-to-date-trendy. They also don't feel dated or old fashioned. Honestly, good aesthetic that fits the hotel. The 1st floor pool area is well kept and relaxing. The restaurants are great and the staff is super warm and friendly. Definitely worth the price and would definitely stay here again!

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, guests, hospitality.
completion:
Amazing staff.  Felt very welcomed.  Valet / Bellman in both areas superb at their job, thank you for taking care of our vehicle and luggage. Guest services / night audit April was very informative and helpful upon arrival and when we needed assistance with our  settings for the A/C. Don Ricos restaurant superb food and beverage staff. Thank you to the whole team.
I enjoyed all the guest areas .  I enjoyed the ocean view room for the view and very spacious.  Dated lamps are worn  and little things around the room. The only thing I didn’t like was the musty smell of water, wet carpet.  The bathroom could of been cleaned better. Behind the toilet where there’s caulking is mildew.  My room was on the fourth floor ocean view so we had the ultimate view.  I really enjoyed it here. I hope the hotel will be updated soon. I work in hospitality and I understand that this industry was very much affected by the pandemic and not mention storms that haven’t helped and it’s slowly getting more people hired and getting the experience staff hired and trying make revenue as well.   Keeping guests feeling comfortable and welcomed is always number one.  I will be a repeat guest.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, guests, pet.
completion: Well opening the curtains to the ocean couldn't get better, watching the 🌅 sunrise and 🌄 sunset just amazing. Now, the size of the room for the price and the pictures could be better adding that the room did not have a balcony and the bathroom was perfect for my 5 feet even but not for a taller longer leg person. I was hoping pet friendly meant everywhere but we har to leave my emotional support mini golden doodle in the room several times. The valet parking system needs more employees poor guys/gals they are overworked and same for bellmen. Keep updating and working on the AC working in the halls. And make the entire hotel pet friendly or make areas for guests with pets. Overall, we liked it.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotels, hilton, beach.
completion: For being a Hilton I was expecting way more. I understand that usually beach hotels are a little rusty, but again, this is a Hilton. Rooms are ok but outdated. Service was always great! All staff very helpful and nice. The view is great! Loved watching the sun rise and all activity at the beach. Location is great.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hilton, tower.
completion: This hotel is mismanaged and full of hidden fees. Two of the elevators in the south tower have been out of operation for at least a month. It can take up to 20 minutes to get an elevator and there is a line for the elevator at peak times. McDonald's are managed better. The entrance is so small that we had to sit in line out in the road waiting for the hotel. This is a hazard for guests and a liability for the hotel. I do not understand why this is a Hilton when it I haven't experienced this mismanagement at extended stay. The pool was nice but not very deep. The hot tub was small. The parking was extremely expensive. The food in the hotel is also expensive. There are no proper heaters in the rooms so if it is cold, you will suffer. We called the engineer and he said they have toaster ovens for heaters in the rooms. His quote. Too many hidden fees and too high of a cost for having half elevators working and being forced to wait out in the street to get to the hotel.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, ocean, rooms.
completion:
We Stayed Here almost a week during the Rolex 24 and opted for the Ocean View.

Really enjoyed this hotel.  The beds were just right for our extended stay.  Close to lots of food options.  We ate and drank at Don Rico’s in the lobby quite a few times and enjoyed that.

The rooms are nothing spectacular but are decently clean with no signs of bed bugs.  Showers work ok, sinks don’t back up on you and the view was awesome.

We slept with our sliding door open every night so we could feel the cool ocean breeze and hear the waves all night.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, accommodations, resort.
completion: Accommodations are clean. Pool and hot tub clean. No room microwave. Cable TV 👍🏻. Comfortable bed. Clean bathroom. A/C loud on and off. Room walls a little thin/ hear neighbors and their TV. Nice beach view. Easy in and out. Food on site $$$. Starbucks on site $$. Resort fee and valet $$$. Hotel needs some renovations/updating. Expensive for the accommodations.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: beach, hotel, place.
completion: Best location! Has everything. Staff is super!! Hotel though is older, needs a cleaning on small things and a renovation. But still the best place on the beach to stay. Remember, it’s an older hotel in today’s world and needs a renovation. Best place to stay on the beach.

prompt: Write a 3.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hilton, tower.
completion: The room that we got on the north tower was in need of repair. My family's expectations of a Hilton Hotel were not met to say the least for the high price we paid. The floor tile was broken and the closet door was off the railing. The common areas were very nice and the staff were friendly but the room itself was a shame especially the bathroom.

prompt: Write a 1.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotels, hotel, guests.
completion:
This place was way below our expectations we decided to spend a little more and stay at a known hotel line rather than risking it with an unknown place just to enjoy our weekend away. And we were WRONG, the picture attached of the rusted bathroom equipment was just 1 of many unacceptable issues.

Service: the worse, upon arrival they were very flat not very welcoming this place is huge with different things going on and no one even told me anything I had to figure out where and what everything was. But that’s not even the issue. House keeping is almost impossible to get I’ve never been to a hotel where you have to call a specific number to request it within a restricted time frame. Zero small bathroom/shower supplies. We were charged 40 dollars a night for valet parking and no one even answered the phone when we had a dinner date to get our car so we had to walk to the actual place then wait for the car.

The restaurants and bars mind you that are already over priced have awful service because they are SOOOO understaffed this one poor man was literally running the entire Resturant and bar while getting yelled at. The one pool bar they had, there were like 10-12 people wrapped around in a line just to get one drink by the pool in the hot heat so we said forget it the second time 😩 The first night on arrival when I tried to take a quick rinse/shower  the water stopped draining.

But other than that the room wasn’t dirty the sheets were clean that’s all I gave you guys sadly. And I’m not one to leave reviewed but I HAD to give the next people a heads up.

Also i mentioned it to the manager and she didn’t even offer anything she said “I’ll talk to house keeping “. Most other places would at the very least try to make up for the bad service to protect their standards .. not at all.

If I could do it again I would reserve at the other ocean front hotels. My partner and I checked out the other ones and they actually looked really nice and inviting like they wanted to earn guests. I guess these big name hotels feel like because they have the name they don’t have to try as hard now? Not sure.

completion: My oceanfront view was breathtaking. My sister surprised me with this hotel stay for my birthday and I was overwhelmed. I stayed on the 11th floor and everything was above exceptional, from the very clean room and wonderful breakfast staff.

prompt: Write a 1.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hotels, hilton.
completion:

prompt: Write a 1.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hotel, hilton, rooms.
completion: First off.....we decided to stay AFTER spending $300 on a time share tour that we are not going to do because after calling to book it over the last 3 months theres no availability every time we call. So.... Being Diamond members who decided to spend over 400,000 points on our room. We asked to extend our stay when we first got here and was declined. But as Diamond members we are guaranteed a room if requested within 48 hrs. Secondly, in our suite since we arrived the A/C has not worked. It has gotten up to 75-76 and has been set at 64-60 respectively our poor little one is all sweaty during her nap, it took having engineers come to our room 3 times over 2 days without an offer to switch rooms until they fixed it towards the end of our trip. At night it got a little chilly so I asked for 2 more blankets and they were out! So they gave us some bed sheets?!?!The Wi-Fi is absolutely garbage! It cuts out like every 10 minutes, then you have to re-sign in. The beds were absolutely horrible and honestly as a Diamond member it didn't feel much different than a regular member. I will say the employees from the valet to the room engineers/maintenence and in between were kind. But, overall I'm pretty upset about spending over 400,000 points as a Diamond member. And I am seriously considering switching credit cards with a different hotel chain! I will be following up with Hilton corporate if no refund of points are offered. I will update if/when I hear word.

prompt: Write a 1.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hiltons, hilton, staff.
completion:
My family of 6 just finished a 5 night stay, to say we were underwhelmed is an understatement. We happen to be a hardworking blue-collar family, so when paying $629.00 a night for a suite at the Hilton, we were really excited to experience a stay that's above average to our typical Redroof or Days Inn stay. At arrival I was declined a military discount, not absolutely a deal breaker as I was told I was already receiving good deal by the front desk. Of course we were in town for a work conference and were also denied the block rate supposedly due to the fact that we had a suite (the only Accessible room available at the time of our reservation). Next, we arrived in our suite and had to use the restroom after our 16 hours of travel, only to find that housekeeping has definitely not done a very thorough job cleaning the toilet. Ok, fine. I pulled out some Clorox wipes and took care of it myself. At the same time, we noticed the room was excessively hot, so after settling in we called the front desk and notified them that the ac was not working, she said she would send an engineer up to check it out. At 230am when we still hadn't seen the engineer, we went to bed leaving the door open for a breeze to cool the room off. (The ac automatically turns off when the patio door is open, this was not the reason our ac was not working as we had complied with troubleshooting from the front desk) It wasn't until 2 more calls to the front desk and almost 2 days into our stay that the ac was worked on and worked at least enough to make the room bearable. Next up....showers, nothing like stepping out of a nice warm steamy shower to briefly look up when drying off and seeing black mold.......gross. Room service was not an option during our stay, a bit of a bummer as the kids were looking forward experiencing that. On the flip side we ended up dining down in the Don Ricos. It was a bit pricey at $14.00 for a pb&j sandwich with fries for the kids, needless to say there are lots of other options outside the Hilton for food choices and we made that choice for the remainder of our stay. The kid zone was non existent, the kids were really bummed about that as it was one of the reasons we had chosen to stay at the Hilton. The elevators were in a state of broken or in repair a couple times during our stay leading to extra long wait times to get to the lobby. We made our reservation for 6, had a suite for 6, paid the additional fee to have breakfast included but were informed it only included 4 so we didn't dine as a family for breakfast.

The good: At check in the kids were all given a fun craft to do, which they did and thoroughly enjoyed. Our request for extra towels and blankets was met quickly and our interactions with the staff were pleasant. The location was great as it's was very central for the things we needed to do. The beach was fantastic even though access was very limited due to damaged walk ways.  Last but most important, the unobstructed view of the ocean from our suite was fantastic.

Lesson learned, we won't be returning.

UPDATE: I called the number provided by the Hiltons response to my review. I was quickly forwarded to the manager on duty without any prolonged holding. Brooke I think, (I hope that's how her name is spelled) spoke with me for about 20 min as I recounted our stay with them and the reasons for my review. She was open to hearing what I had to say and did not discount or deny the experience we had, which was refreshing! At the end of the conversation, she let me know I would receive a partial refund (which I have received). She handled my call with complete professionalism and kindness.

prompt: Write a 4.0 stars Google Maps review about a Hotel, with the following keywords: hilton, amenities, resort.
completion:
Like many have said, the location is perfect, staff is nice, lobby area is nice… but the rooms are lacking.

We had an oceanview room with a king in the south tower. It was spacious and we had no problem with the air temp or water, but it felt very outdated and the bed was not great.
